# Walkthrough - Client-Side Routing Implementation & Deployment

## Goal
Implement client-side routing to provide unique URLs for each feature and deploy the updated application to Cloudflare.

## Changes

### 1. [App.tsx](file:///i:/Workflow/n8n/Workflow/Backups/web-fontend-v2/src/App.tsx) Refactoring
- **Integration**: Wrapped the application with `BrowserRouter`.
- **Routing**: Replaced `renderContent` conditional logic with `Routes` and `Route` components.
- **Tools Layout**: Introduced [ToolsLayout](file:///i:/Workflow/n8n/Workflow/Backups/web-fontend-v2/src/App.tsx#136-175) to handle individual tool routes (`/instagram`, `/zing-mp3`, etc.).

### 2. Navigation Update
- **Header/Footer**: Switched to [Link](file:///i:/Workflow/n8n/Workflow/Backups/web-fontend-v2/src/components/SoundCloudDownload.tsx#47-75) components.
- **Active State**: Implemented `useLocation` for active link highlighting.

### 3. Deployment Configuration
- **Cloudflare**: Added [_redirects](file:///i:/Workflow/n8n/Workflow/Backups/web-fontend-v2/dist/_redirects) file for SPA routing.
- **Scripts**: Added `"deploy": "npm run build && wrangler pages deploy dist --project-name tai-video"` to [package.json](file:///i:/Workflow/n8n/Workflow/Backups/web-fontend-v2/package.json).

## Usage
To deploy updates in the future, simply run:
```bash
npm run deploy
```
This command will automatically build the project and deploy it to the `tai-video` Cloudflare project.
